The Australian College of Pharmacy is one of three major providers of continuing professional development (CPD) programmes for pharmacists in Australiaâ€”the others being the Pharmaceutical Society of Australia (PSA) and The Society of Hospital Pharmacists of Australia (SHPA). The college has been educating Australian pharmacists since 1978. The college is the second largest organisation in the Australian industry, behind the PSA but larger than The Pharmacy Guild of Australia.
Members of the college are entitled to use the postnominal MACP, associate fellows AFACP, while fellows of the college use the FACP.
